Package edu.kit.unwwi.checkpoints.qemu.models.memory

Klasse MemoryMapping

java.lang.Object
edu.kit.unwwi.checkpoints.qemu.models.memory.MemoryMapping
Alle implementierten Schnittstellen:
Serializable, Comparable<MemoryMapping>
public class MemoryMapping extends Object implements Comparable<MemoryMapping>, Serializable
A class representing a single memory mapping inside the TLB. The equals- and hashCode-methods are create in a way to allow for searching through a hashtable by the virtual address, meaning, when testing for equality, only the virtual address gets tested.

    • MemoryMapping

      public MemoryMapping(long virtualAddress, long physicalAddress, long size, char[] flags)
      Creates a new memory mapping from the provided data.
      Parameter:
      virtualAddress - The starting address of the virtual page of this mapping.
      physicalAddress - The starting address of the physical frame of this mapping.
      size - The size of the mapped space.
      flags - The flags set for this space.
